<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1613,2035]" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">
In 1949, he provided an illustration of the male terminalia in ventral view on which the subgenital plates are clearly drawn. He did not dissect the type’s genitalia. Here, we provide for the first time, the detailed illustration and description of the male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[526,657,1685,1711]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Figs 44–48</figureCitation>
) from the 
<typeStatus box="[779,879,1685,1711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">paratype</typeStatus>
. Pictures of the 
<typeStatus box="[1065,1163,1685,1711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[1221,1317,1685,1711]" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">paratype</typeStatus>
with their labels are provided (
<figureCitation box="[379,510,1721,1748]" captionStart="FIGURES 36–43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1921,1946]" captionTargetBox="[187,1397,172,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[185,1402,170,1909]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 36–43. Poeciloterpa fusca, holotype. 36. Habitus, dorsal view. 37. frontal view. 38. lateral view. 39. Labels. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype, male 40. Habitus, dorsal view. 41. frontal view. 42. lateral view. 43. Labels. Photographed by Laurent Fauvre © 2018 MNHN." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055956/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Figs 36–43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="301" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1613,2035]" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[396,482,1757,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). In lateral view, pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[786,868,1756,1783]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
) dorsal margin longer than ventral margin, dorsal margin concaved in middle, ventral margin regularly curved, posterior margin undulating slightly; Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[160,242,1829,1856]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, Sickles blade shaped with sharp apex pointing dorsally, entire length covered with hairs; lateral plate with sharp angle pointing anteroventrally. Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[893,976,1865,1891]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
) with dorsal margin largely convex then abruptly curving up, ventral margin finishing posteriorly by a sharp tip. Set of setae located on roundest part of dorsal margin and ventral margin of paramere.Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[758,839,1937,1963]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–49" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[184,1408,188,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[173,1414,170,1918]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 44–49. Poeciloterpa fusca, paratype. 44. Male terminalia, lateral view. 45. Pygofer and anal tube, lateral view. 46. Subgenital plate, lateral view, LP: lateral plate, IP: intermediate plate. 47. Paramere, lateral view. 48. Aedeagus, lateral view, ae: apical extension, pp: posterior protrusion. 49. Tegmina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3055962/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="301">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) dorsal margin curving strongly but regularly without any drastic break, apical extension tapering regularly into a sharp apex pointing anteroventrally, posterior protrusion long and narrow, curving abruptly down at ¾ of its length, posteroventral protrusion absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
